RBC Capital Names Barclays’s Goldberg to Co-Head U.S. Unit

-- B y   S e a n   B .   P a s t e r n a k
-- 
2011-08-04T14:12:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/rbc-capital-names-goldberg-to-co-head-u-s-capital-market-unit.html
RBC Capital Markets, the investment-
banking unit of  Royal Bank of Canada (RY) , named former Barclays
Capital executive  Michael Goldberg  a managing director and co-
head of its U.S. equity-capital markets group.  Goldberg, 46, will co-lead the group with Joe Morea, RBC
Capital said in an e-mailed statement today. He will report to
Blair Fleming, U.S. investment-banking head. Goldberg was a
managing director at Barclays’s equity-capital markets group.  He is RBC’s second hire from Barclays in as many days.
Steve Feinstein, previously a managing director at Barclays,
will head the corporate-derivatives marketing group, the
Toronto-based lender said yesterday.  Royal Bank, Canada’s largest lender by assets, has been
building its U.S. investment-banking group. The unit now
includes 370 people and has about 120 people in the U.K.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sean B. Pasternak in Toronto at 
 spasternak@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
